A UCB may declare dividend provided it fulfils conditions outlined as under:
(i) It shall comply with applicable regulatory capital requirement;
(ii) NNPA ratio shall be less than five per cent, after making all necessary provisions (including provisions required as per assessment made by the Reserve Bank in the last inspection report), for the financial year for which dividend is proposed;
(iii) There is no default in maintenance of Cash Reserve Ratio (CRR) / Statutory Liquidity Ratio (SLR) during the financial year for which dividend is proposed;
(iv) All required provisions have been made for NPAs, investments and other assets as per prudential and accounting norms; and
(v) Dividend shall be paid out of the net profit, of the financial year for which dividend is being paid, after making all statutory and other provisions and adjustment for accumulated losses in full.

